20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-millennial-bosses-manage-gen-z-workers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20true%20of%20the%20younger%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20you%20should%20leave%20pay%20out%20of%20your%20response%20when%20asked%20why%20you%20want%20to%20work%20for%20a%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELalgee%20said%20companies%20should%20be%20empathetic%20to%20financial%20struggles%20and%20high%20inflation.%20But%2C%20he%20cautioned%20that%20making%20the%20job%20about%20money%20could%20create%20the%20perception%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquadrupled-salary-big-tech-job-hopping-negotiating-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob-hopping%20for%20higher%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20bringing%20up%20compensation%20when%20asked%20about%20interest%20in%20a%20job%2C%20Lalgee%20advises%20candidates%20to%20prepare%20a%20response%20highlighting%20the%20company's%20mission%20or%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20really%20committed%20to%20the%20mission%20and%20the%20culture%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20will%20believe%20that%20you're%20gonna%20be%20more%20dedicated%20to%20the%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Lalgee%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22506e51a0-3dc6-4eb9-8d55-e598a8d6ba9d%5C%22%3EWhy%20you%20left%20your%20last%20company%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worst%20thing%20a%20candidate%20can%20do%20is%20go%20on%20a%20tangent%20about%20their%20previous%20or%20current%20company%2C%20Lalgee%20told%20BI.%20The%20advice%20may%20seem%20obvious%2C%20but%20Lalgee%20said%20it's%20easy%20to%20get%20carried%20away%20when%20you're%20a%20little%20nervous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20always%20be%20a%20red%20flag%20when%20they're%20considering%20you%20against%20other%20candidates%2C%26quot%3B%20Lalgee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELalgee%20said%20in%20his%20video%20that%20candidates%20should%20speak%20positively%20about%20past%20experiences%20while%20adding%20that%20they're%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20candidate%20feels%20compelled%20to%20be%20honest%20about%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-seek-therapy-toxic-bosses-mental-health-anxiety-study-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegative%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lalgee%20told%20BI%20they%20can%20say%20it%20wasn't%20a%20match%20or%20a%20culture%20fit.%20He%20then%20recommends%20pivoting%20the%20conversation%20to%20explain%20how%20the%20current%20company%20aligns%20better%20with%20the%20goals%20or%20values%20that%20the%20candidate%20is%20looking%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a6d8d893-c046-4cdf-a219-ee711303870e%5C%22%3EPlans%20for%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELalgee%20said%20it%20may%20be%20tempting%20to%20be%20honest%20when%20asked%20about%20your%20longterm%20plans%2C%20whether%20that%20be%20grad%20school%2C%20starting%20a%20family%2C%20or%20changing%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20recruiters%20or%20hiring%20managers%20ask%20this%2C%20they're%20looking%20for%20you%20to%20talk%20about%20your%20future%20at%20the%20company%2C%20Lalgee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Brecruitment%20is%20expensive%26quot%3B%20and%20companies%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20want%20people%20that%20they're%20gonna%20invest%20in%26quot%3B%20that%20will%20end%20up%20leaving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f58a5493-d301-45d9-9412-05930bc3f05e%5C%22%3ESalary%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELalgee%20said%20hiring%20managers%20shouldn't%20be%20asking%20how%20much%20you%20make%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20they%20do%2C%20you%20shouldn't%20tell%20the%20truth.%20Instead%2C%20you%20should%20state%20the%20range%20of%20salary%20you're%20targeting%2C%20Lalgee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECandidates%20should%20give%20a%20%2420%2C000%20to%20%2430%2C000%20range%20of%20what%20they're%20looking%20for%2C%20Lalgee%20said.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-steps-negotiate-higher-salary-soaring-job-market-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHe%20also%20warns%20not%20to%20lowball%20yourself%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20make%20sure%20the%20starting%20number%20is%20your%20midpoint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20way%2C%20if%20they%20do%20lowball%20you%2C%20which%20they're%20doing%20a%20lot%20right%20now%20because%20of%20the%20state%20of%20the%20market%2C%20you%20at%20least%20haven't%20truly%20lowballed%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20Lalgee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d606b8f-3f9a-4bea-b464-ffba45db709c%5C%22%3EWhether%20you're%20interviewing%20at%20other%20places%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELalgee%20said%20mentioning%20you're%20interviewing%20at%20other%20companies%20can%20give%20you%20negotiating%20power.%20Candidates%20should%20respond%20%26quot%3Byes%26quot%3B%20or%20say%20that%20they're%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20asked%20if%20they're%20interviewing%20at%20other%20places%2C%20Lalgee%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20in%20demand%20you%20are%2C%20the%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Lalgee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20sharing%20specific%20details%20isn't%20necessary%2C%20Lalgee%20said%20he's%20never%20seen%20this%20strategy%20backfire%20and%20warns%20against%20the%20opposite%20approach%20of%20telling%20the%20company%20that%20all%20your%20eggs%20are%20in%20their%20basket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffive-lies-to-tell-interview-recruiting-expert-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723123731000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b39a90393cd3c8629c0e03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffive-lies-to-tell-interview-recruiting-expert-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20interview%20process%2C%20candidates%20should%20consider%20telling%20these%20five%20white%20lies%2C%20Joel%20Lalgee%20said.%22%2C%22author%22