%209%25%2C%20less%20than%20that%20of%20the%20average%20man.%20The%20body%20fat%20means%20less%20weight%20to%20carry.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falev-kelter-olympic-womens-rugby-us-training-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erugby%20players%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20benefit%20from%20packing%20on%20mass%20and%20muscle%20to%20help%20absorb%20contact%20from%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20sports%20such%20as%20weightlifting%2C%20boxing%2C%20and%20judo%20are%20divided%20into%20weight%20classes%2C%20so%20athletes%20have%20to%20consider%20how%20to%20balance%20the%20optimal%20amount%20of%20muscle%20with%20the%20right%20overall%20size%20to%20perform%20their%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuscle%20mass%20is%20just%20one%20factor%20in%20elite%20competition%2C%20as%20variables%20like%20skill%2C%20stamina%2C%20and%20much%20more%20all%20play%20into%20determining%20who%20makes%20the%20podium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECompared%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20us%2C%20they%20have%20superhuman%20grip%20strength.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20of%20hand%20made%20into%20tight%20fist%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b265de393cd3c8629ba984%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Natalie%20Ammari%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20probably%20don't%20put%20your%20entire%20body%20weight%20on%20your%20hands%20very%20often.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparis-olympics-womens-gymnastics-leotards-hidden-details-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOlympic%20gymnasts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20frequently%20stand%20on%2C%20spring%20from%2C%20swing%20from%2C%20and%20even%20catch%20their%20spinning%20bodies%20with%20their%20hands%2C%20so%20they%20need%20exceptional%20grip%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20grip%20is%20so%20critical%20