iv%3E%3Cdiv%3EExercise%20gives%20immune%20systems%20a%20boost%2C%20but%20Olympians%20probably%20don't%20have%20super%20immunity.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Microscopic%20image%20of%20immunity%20fighting%20toxins%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b26614b4912df3ae194577%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Natalie%20Ammari%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EExercise%20is%20great%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-to-boost-immunity-avoid-sickness-during-holiday-travel-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmune%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20just%20how%20much%20is%20up%20for%20debate.%20And%20given%20the%20extreme%20mental%20and%20physical%20stress%20that%20Olympians%20can%20endure%2C%20it's%20possible%20that%20could%20overturn%20the%20immune-boosting%20benefits%20of%20regular%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20universal%20consensus%20that%20the%20immune%20system%20benefits%20from%20regular%2C%20moderate-intensity%20exercise%2C%20said%20Richard%20Simpson%2C%20an%20exercise%20physiologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20workout%20regularly%20tend%20to%20have%20less%20inflammation%2C%20less%20risk%20of%20disease%2C%20and%20respond%20better%20to%20vaccines.%20Simpson%20is%20looking%20into%20why%20that's%20the%20case%20by%20researching%20how%20immune%20cells%20circulate%20in%20the%20body%2C%20one%20of%20many%20mechanisms%20involved%20with%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20single%20time%20you%20exercise%2C%20you%20mobilize%20and%20redistribute%20billions%20of%20immune%20cells%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Even%20a%2020-minute%20workout%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fimmune-booster%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eamplifies%20this%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20still%20unclear%20is%20whether%20elite%20athletes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Fjournals%2Fphysiology%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffphys.2019.01550%2Ffull%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrigger%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-over-exercise-does-body-brain-health-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoo%20much%20inflammation%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20over-exercise.%20%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20is%20that%20you're%20just%20beating%20your%20body%20up%20so%20much%20that%20you're%20causing%20inflammation%2C%26quot%3B%20Simpson%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20releasing%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20stress%20hormones%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20that%20can%20negatively%20affect%20the%20immune%20system%20and%20leave%20you%20more%20susceptible%20to%20illness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20said%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20factors%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F17465622%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20make%3C%2Fa%3E%20marathon%20runners%20or%20Olympians%20more%20prone%20to%20infections%2C%20like%20high%20levels%20of%20stress%20or%20just%20being%20exposed%20to%20big%20crowds.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20a%20very%20controversial%20topic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-olympic-athletes-bodies-minds-different-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723122782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b29e97b4912df3ae197b63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-olympic-athletes-bodies-minds-different-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Watching%20the%20Olympics%20might%20make%20you%20wonder%20how%20they%20do%20it.%20What%20sets%20these%20athletes%20apart%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20us%3F%20Science%20offers%20a%2