usted%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20Peace%20noted.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnWang%20faces%20up%20to%2025%20years%20in%20prison%2C%20when%20he%20is%20to%20be%20sentenced%20on%20January%209%20next%20year.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Shujun%20Wang%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnWang%2C%20an%20American%20citizen%2C%20has%20been%20settled%20in%20New%20York%20since%20the%201990s%20after%20his%20stint%20as%20a%20visiting%20university%20scholar%20of%20East%20Asian%20studies%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20commemorate%20figures%20linked%20to%20the%201989%20Tiananmen%20Square%20uprising%2C%20he%20helped%20found%20a%20pro-democracy%20group%20in%202006%20in%20the%20Flushing%20neighbourhood%20of%20Queens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHu%20Yaobang%20and%20Zhao%20Ziyang%20Memorial%20Foundation%20is%20named%20for%20two%20leaders%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20in%20the%201980s.%20As%20per%20its%20official%20website%2C%20the%20group's%20mission%20is%20to%20promote%20China's%20%26quot%3Bconstitutional%20transformation.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20prosecutors%20said%20that%20Wang%20used%20his%20position%20and%20status%20among%20the%20Chinese%20community%20to%20act%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccovert%20intelligence%20asset%20in%20his%20own%20community%2C%E2%80%9D%20since%20at%20least%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWang%2C%20according%20to%20the%20prosecutors%2C%20was%20ordered%20to%20collect%20information%20about%20topics%20and%20people%20the%20Chinese%20government%20deemed%20undesirable.%20Later%2C%20he%20passed%20on%20this%20information%20to%20his%20handlers%20via%20in-person%20meetings%20as%20well%20as%20written%20correspondence%2C%20including%20%E2%80%9Cdiaries%2C%E2%80%9D%20describing%20his%20interactions%20with%20prominent%20activists%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEllen%20Sise%2C%20in%20the%20opening%20statements%2C%20noted%20that%20Wang%20led%20a%20%26quot%3Bdouble%20life%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20portra